  "prompt": "Where can I get audiobooks for free in English?",
  "response": "There are several websites and platforms where you can access free audiobooks in English. Here are some options:\n\n1. **LibriVox**: This is a volunteer-driven project that offers free public domain audiobooks read by volunteers from around the world. You can find a wide range of classic literature.\n\n2. **Project Gutenberg**: In addition to eBooks, Project Gutenberg offers a selection of audiobooks, many of which are produced by LibriVox. \n\n3. **Internet Archive**: This digital library has a large collection of free audiobooks, including many public domain titles.\n\n4. **Open Culture**: Open Culture curates a list of free audiobooks available online, linking to various sources.\n\n5. **Spotify**: Some users create playlists of audiobooks and share them on Spotify. You can search for audiobooks and often find classics or popular titles.\n\n6. **YouTube**: Many classic audiobooks are uploaded to YouTube, either as full readings or as animated or illustrated versions.\n\n7. **Audible Free Trial**: While Audible is a subscription service, they offer a free trial which typically allows you to download one or more audiobooks for free during the trial period.\n\n8. **ManyBooks**: They provide a selection of public domain audiobooks alongside their eBook offerings.\n\n9. **Libby/OverDrive**: If you have a library card, you may be able to access audiobooks through Libby or OverDrive, which allow you to borrow audiobooks from your local library.\n\nMake sure to check the copyright status of the audiobooks, as some might be available for free legally, while others could be restricted.",
